text:
Went for breakfast/lunch because it is famous and we got $5 off coupon for it. Average buffet at most in Las Vegas. Still a 3-star for the low price we paid.

Pros:
- No line at all at 10 am on 12/26!
- Breakfast after coupon only cost $10 per person before tax and tip;
- Good varieties;
- Chinese station: shrimp dumpling, duck, BBQ pork;
- Italian station;

Cons:
- Average to so-so taste for most dishes in the other stations;
- Crabs not fresh;
- "Deep Sea Scallps" were made of cheap fake crab meat (starch);
- Desserts are not delicate enough (they looked better than they tasted);

I wouldn't complain for the price I paid but would not go there at full prices.
